cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

The paper deals with computer vision and robotics, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The focus on mid-level visual representations and learning active tasks suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The use of Deep Reinforcement Learning frameworks suggests that cs.RO (Robotics) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses sample efficiency and generalization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the focus on active tasks suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) could also be a relevant sub-category.
